2. Ethical Use Restrictions

   The software must not be used, directly or indirectly, for:

   a. Military operations, weapons systems, or defense applications,
      including logistics, targeting, command and control systems, or
      any operational support in armed conflict.

   b. Intelligence operations or surveillance programs targeting
      civilian populations.

   c. Systems designed to repress freedom of expression, association,
      assembly, due process, or other internationally recognized human
      rights.

   d. Projects that facilitate war crimes, crimes against humanity,
      genocide, ethnic cleansing, forced displacement, or similar
      serious violations of international humanitarian law.

   These restrictions are perpetual and survive any future relicensing
   of the software by the Licensor.


